  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali133-kilavi">itu "varaivu uṭampaṭṭōrk kaṭāval vēṇṭiṉum" eṉpataṉāṟ ṟalaivaṉ teruḷātavaṉait teruṭṭi varaivukaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali133">
                <l>māmalar muṇṭakan tillaiyō ṭoruṅkuṭaṉ </l>
                <l>kāṉa laṇinta vuyarmaṇa lekkarmēṟ </l>
                <l>cīrmiku ciṟappiṉōṉ maramutaṟ kaicērtta </l>
                <l>nīrmali karakampōṟ paḻantūṅku muṭattāḻaip </l>
                <l>pūmalarn tavaipōlap puḷḷalkun tuṟaivakēḷ;</l>
                <l rend="space">āṟṟuta leṉpatoṉ ṟalantavark kutavutal </l>
                <l>pōṟṟuta leṉpatu puṇarntāraip piriyāmai </l>
                <l>paṇpeṉap paṭuvatu pāṭaṟin toḻukuta </l>
                <l>laṉpeṉap paṭuvatu taṉkiḷai ceṟāmai </l>
                <l>yaṟiveṉap paṭuvatu pētaiyār coṉṉōṉṟal </l>
                <l>ceṟiveṉap paṭuvatu kūṟiyatu maṟāmai </l>
                <l>niṟaiyeṉap paṭuvatu maṟaipiṟa raṟiyāmai </l>
                <l>muṟaiyeṉap paṭuvatu kaṇṇōṭā tuyirvauval </l>
                <l>poṟaiyeṉap paṭuvatu pōṟṟāraip poṟuttal; </l>
                <l rend="space">āṅkatai yaṟintaṉi rāyiṉeṉ ṟōḻi </l>
                <l>naṉṉuta ṉalaṉuṇṭu tuṟattal koṇka </l>
                <l>tīmpā luṇṭavar  koḷkalam varaitali </l>
                <l>ṉiṉṟalai varuntiyā ṭuyarañ </l>
                <l>ceṉṟaṉai kaḷaimō pūṇkaniṉ ṟērē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Oh man from the ghat, where the birds rest, like flowers in bloom,</l>
                <l>on the bent coconut trees from which fruits hang, like pots full of water</l>
                <l>which the hand of a superior man full of excellence  has joined to the trunk of the tree,</l>
                <l>on the high sand dunes adorned with a seashore grove</l>
                <l corresp="1-5">of dark-flowered Muṇṭakam tree together with Tillai trees, listen:</l>
                <l>Comforting, that is helping to something those who are destitute,</l>
                <l>protecting, that is not separating from those one is united with,</l>
                <l>character, that is conducting oneself while knowing what is proper,</l>
                <l>love, that is not being at odds with one’s relatives,</l>
                <l>knowledge, that is enduring the words of fools,</l>
                <l>being close, that is not forgetting what one has been told,</l>
                <l>self-control, that is not knowing the secrets of others,</l>
                <l>order, that is snatching lives without feeling compassion,</l>
                <l corresp="6-14">patience, that is bearing those who are inattentive.</l>
                <l>If you thus have understood those, oh man from the sea, </l>
                <l>because abandoning my friend after having consumed the beauty of [her] good forehead</l>
                <l>is [like] somebody’s having drunk the sweet milk [and] discarding  the vessel that held [it],</l>
                <l>you who have gone remove the sorrow</l>
                <l corresp="15-19">of her who suffers on your account. Let your chariot be yoked.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
